{
  "texts": [
    "At the tissue scale, systems that must be considered include neural, cardiovascular, and respiratory, but also their dysfunctions, such as cancer.",
    "Whether investigating the intricate networks within the human brain or the simpler wiring maps of organisms like C. elegans or Drosophila Melanogaster, the objective remains consistent: to elucidate the interconnections and organization of neurons and regions at the mesoscale.",
    "Several studies have focused on examining neural connections within an organism's brain, commonly referred to as the connectome 90.",
    "Functional imaging techniques are utilized to explore the relationship among activities in specific brain https://doi.org/10.1038/s41746-024-01402-3 areas 91.",
    "The analytical and computational tools from network theory allow us to build maps of structural and functional connections, revealing characteristics of complex networks-such as small-world topology, highly connected hubs, and modularity-that manifest at both the whole-brain and cellular scales [92] [93] [94]."
  ]
}